room_title: Escape room "Escape from Alcatraz" by San Jose Room Escape in San Jose
room_address: 1620 Oakland Road, Suite D203 San Jose, CA 95131
room_description:
One of the United States' most notorious criminals, Robert Stroud, known as "Birdman of Alcatraz", has died after serving a life sentence in solitary confinement at Alcatraz. After Robert's death, his jailers and fellow inmates hear weird sounds and see strange lights in his dog hole. Then they disappear.
Imprisonment is the start of the story. Two participants are locked in the prison cell that Birdman died, dark and cold. You and your audacious team members need to break all the safety guards to rescue your friends and get yourself out of Alcatraz in under 60 minutes.
